**YCF Cubic B-Spline Yield Curve Application**: Excel VBA application written by Zhuoshi Liu and Moorad Choudhry. Derives spot and forward rate yield curves from government bond prices or money market rates. Calculates fair prices of bonds and swap contracts. Uses VRP cubic spline methodology following Bank of England (Anderson and Sleath 2001) and US Federal Reserve model (Waggoner 1997). Models instantaneous forward rate curve as a natural cubic spline.

## Afterword (pp. 993-994)

"The profession of banking is an honourable one. To be given a responsibility at any level of a banking institution is to be entrusted with a valuable part of society's well-being."

Matthew Syed, *Bounce: The Myth of Talent and the Power of Practice* (London: Fourth Estate, 2010) — quoted on the primacy of experience and practice over innate ability; expertise is built through dedicated effort, not natural talent alone. Banking competence must be cultivated the same way.

"The underlying message remains: the first principle of good banking is to have principles. Or, as the motto of the London Stock Exchange puts it: *my word is my bond.*"

